Since $\angle APB = 40^\circ$, $\angle RAP + \angle RBP = 180^\circ - 40^\circ = 140^\circ$.  Then $2 \angle RAP = 140^\circ$, so $\angle RAP = 70^\circ$.  Therefore, $\angle RAT = 2 \angle RAP = 140^\circ$.

Since $\angle RAT$ and $\angle AOB$ are supplementary, $\angle AOB = 180^\circ - 140^\circ = 40^\circ$.

